did.unittitle: Whitney Humanities Center, Yale University, records

repository.corpname: Yale University. Department of Manuscripts and Archives

did.abstract: The records consist of correspondence, memoranda, student files, senior essays, and subject and administrative files documenting the operations of the Whitney Humanities Center. Topics include the Humanities Advisory Committee, the A. Whitney Griswold Faculty Research Fund, the Frederick W. Hilles Publication Fund, the National Institute for the Humanities, the Scholar of the House program, and the center's undergraduate programs.

odd.head: General note
odd.p: Forms part of Yale Record Group 37 (YRG 37), Records of associations, institutes, centers, and organizations affiliated with Yale University.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Access to the records is restricted. See Collection Contents for details.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Copyright for materials authored or otherwise produced as official business of Yale University is retained by Yale University. Copyright status for other collection materials is unknown. Transmission or reproduction of materials protected by U.S. Copyright Law (Title 17, U.S.C.) beyond that allowed by fair use requires the written permission of the copyright owners. Works not in the public domain cannot be commercially exploited without permission of the copyright owners. Responsibility for any use rests exclusively with the user.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Whitney Humanities Center, Yale University, Records (RU 569). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: Yale University records are arranged and described at the accession level by the creating office. The University Archives creates collection level descriptive records, but typically does no further arrangement and description at the accession level.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: The Whitney Humanities Center was established in 1981 as an interdisciplinary institution "designed to enable and enhance research, thinking, and scholarly exchange in all fields of the humanities and throughout [Yale] University."

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The records consist of correspondence, memoranda, student files, senior essays, and subject and administrative files documenting the operations of the Whitney Humanities Center. Topics include the Humanities Advisory Committee, the A. Whitney Griswold Faculty Research Fund, the Frederick W. Hilles Publication Fund, the National Institute for the Humanities, the Scholar of the House program, and the center's undergraduate programs.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The records are arranged by accession.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: The materials are open for research.
